Interface IYahooMediaCommonObjectEntities

Allows an object to implement common Yahoo media entities by representing a set of properties, methods, indexers and events common to Yahoo media syndication resources.

Namespace: Argotic.Extensions.Core
Assembly: Argotic.Extensions.dll
Syntax
public interface IYahooMediaCommonObjectEntities
Remarks

The following properties are optional and may appear as sub-elements of syndication entities, YahooMediaContent and/or YahooMediaGroup.

When a property appears at a shallow level, such as syndication entities, it means that the property should be applied to every media object within its scope. Duplicated properties appearing at deeper levels of the document tree have higher priority over other levels. For example, YahooMediaContent level properties are favored over syndication entity level properties.

The priority level is listed from strongest to weakest: YahooMediaContent, YahooMediaGroup, syndication item entity, syndication feed.

Credits

Gets the entities that contributed to the creation of the media object.

Declaration
Collection<YahooMediaCredit> Credits { get; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<YahooMediaCredit>

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of YahooMediaCredit objects that represent the entities that contributed to the creation of the media object. The default value is an empty collection.
Remarks

Current entities can include people, companies, locations, etc. Specific entities can have multiple roles, and several entities can have the same role. These should appear as distinct YahooMediaCredit entities.

TextSeries

Gets the text transcript, closed captioning, or lyrics for the media object.

Declaration
Collection<YahooMediaText> TextSeries { get; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<YahooMediaText>

A System.Collections.ObjectModel.Collection<T> collection of YahooMediaText objects that represent text transcript, closed captioning, or lyrics for the media object. The default value is an empty collection.
Remarks

Many of these YahooMediaText objects are permitted to provide a time series of text. In such cases, it is encouraged, but not required, that the YahooMediaText objects be grouped by language and appear in time sequence order based on the start time. YahooMediaText objects can have overlapping start and end times.
